<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-09-05T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-09-05T12:00:00-05:00" n="35" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d35">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00111 A.R./26: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Panama</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-09-05T12:00:00-05:00">September
                                    5, 1939—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 1:04 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>92. Department’s telegram No. 69 of September 4, 9 p.m. The procedure
                            envisaged is entirely agreeable to the Panamanian Government which will
                            issue the joint invitation in accordance with suggested text as soon as
                            authorization of the several inviting governments is received either
                            through the Department or directly.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>